<FIRST>r a PM-People-Ramtha     03-02 0193</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Ramtha,0199</SECOND>
<HEAD>`Channeler' Who Speaks to Shirley MacLaine, Linda Evans Divorcing
Husband</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TACOMA, Wash. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   J.Z. Knight, who says a 35,000-year-old
warrior uses her to speak to entertainers Shirley MacLaine, Linda
Evans and others, has filed for divorce from her husband of five
years.
   Mrs. Knight is known as the ``channeler'' for Ramtha, a wise man
and warrior whose voice allegedly is heard through Knight by New Age
followers who pay fees to attend the sessions.
   Knight's estranged husband, Jeffrey Knight, left the family home
near Yelm, about 25 miles south of Tacoma, in October. He is seeking
$10,000 a month in spousal maintenance.
   Through his lawyer, Grant Harken, he said he and his wife had a
premarital agreement to divide assets from their ventures, including
Ramtha Dialogues Inc. and an Arabian horse stud farm.
   He claims Ramtha brings in about $240,000 a month in income from
seminars, book royalties and tape sales. No estimate was available
on revenues from the horses.
   Calls to J.Z. Knight's listed phone numbers at the farm went
unanswered Wednesday night.
   The divorce trial is set for April 10 in Pierce County Superior
Court in Tacoma.
</TEXT>
