<FILEID>AP-NR-03-02-89 0637EST</FILEID>
<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--RunawayCow     03-02 0155</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Runaway Cow,0161</SECOND>
<HEAD>Crashes Through Bank Window</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   You've heard of the bull in the china
shop. How about the cow in the bank?
   A half-dozen First National Bank of Louisville customers were
startled when a cow crashed through a window Tuesday after escaping
from a nearby downtown stockyard.
   ``I was writing the deposit ticket out and I looked up, and in
the window was a big black _ and I looked again _ a cow!'' said
Louis Cox. ``And then it came through the window and it ... sort of
brushed this one guy down on the floor.
   Cox said the animal was foaming at the mouth and his first
thought was that the animal was ``crazy or something.''
   ``She just got scared, that's all,'' said Bruce Pearce, general
manager of the stockyard.
   Except for the shattered window and a backstrain suffered by Cox,
the cow didn't cause any damage.
</TEXT>
