unintended way, that the law ... does not truly mean what it says,''
wrote Waples.
   The prosecutor also cited Goetz's ``outspoken advocacy of arming
citizens with handguns.''
   One of the four youths remains paralyzed from the incident. Goetz
was sentenced Jan. 13 on a weapons conviction.
