<SECOND>PM-Performer Charged,0250</SECOND>
<HEAD>Rock Performer Charged With Disorderly Conduct</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MILWAUKEE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A member of a group called the Toilet Rockers
was charged with disorderly conduct for a performance in which he
allegedly cut himself with glass, exposed himself to the crowd and
defecated on stage.
   ``I acted out my lyrics, nothing more, nothing less,'' said Kevin
M. ``G.G.'' Allin, 32, of Midlothian, Ill. ``I'm just showing people
reality is there. It's there on my stage.''
   Allin was charged Wednesday after a performance the night before
at the Odd Rock Cafe.
   ``If people are going to come to our shows, they've got to have a
strong mind and stomach. If people are sensitive, they'll take one
look at me and leave. I'm sure most people hate me,'' he said.
   He described his performance as theater. ``I've done it before,
but I don't do it at every show,'' he said. ``I don't want to be
predictable.
   ``Sometimes I go off. I go over the edge.''
   Allin said scabs on his forehead were from hitting himself with
the microphone, bruises on his face were from beating himself while
the audience of about 50 looked on and bite marks on his arms were
his own doing.
   John M. Baker, the attorney for nightclub owner John Koshick,
said Koshick had no idea Allin was going to perform the acts that
led to the disorderly conduct charges. ``If he would, he never would
have booked him,'' Baker said.
</TEXT>
