<HEAD>Palestinian Fatally Shot Trying To Stab Soldier</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By ALLYN FISHER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Israeli soldier fatally shot a Palestinian
man who tried to stab another soldier with a knife during house
searches in the occupied Gaza Strip, the army spokesman said today.
   A Palestinian teen-ager was shot and wounded in the leg during a
clash with troops in the seaside strip today, Arab news reports said.
   An Israeli officer, Uri Peles, 26, was injured in the cheek
Wednesday night by a rock thrown by Palestinians as he drove through
Gaza, the army said.
   Soldiers maintained a curfew on the occupied West Bank city of
Nablus, confining nearly all its 120,000 residents indoors for a
seventh straight day.
   The restrictions were imposed Friday after a soldier was killed
by a cement block dropped on his head from a third-story window in
Nablus' marketplace.
