guerrillas in southern Lebanon who were en route to attack targets
in Israel, the army said. The clash occurred about three miles north
of the Israeli-Lebanese border in the western sector of Israel's
self-proclaimed security zone, said an army source, who cannot be
identified under military regulations.
   Marwan Hussein Khawaz, 24, of Tufah in Gaza, shot Wednesday
night, was the 388th Palestinian to die in the 15-month uprising.
Seventeen Israelis, including six soldiers, have also died in the
unrest.
   The army said Khawaz was shot by a soldier ``after he was
identified as trying to attack a soldier with a knife.'' The
incident occurred while troops arrested people in Tufah, the army
said. It said the soldier was not hurt.
   Tufah was also placed under curfew after the shooting, the army
said.
   Troops today opened fire on stone-throwing protesters in Gaza
City's Rimalt quarter, injuring a 17-year-old Palestinian, Arab
reports said.
   The Israeli officer injured by rock-throwing Palestinians in Khan
Yunis was identified by Maariv daily identified as Uri Peles, 26.
