<SECOND>PM-Cocaine Eater,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Man Eats Cocaine As Police Approach, Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOLEDO, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who said he swallowed seven grams of
cocaine to avoid arrest by approaching police officers died of an
overdose two hours later, police reported today.
   Samuel M. McBeth, 36, of Fostoria, ate the drug in a parking lot
Wednesday as two officers investigating suspicious activity
approached the car in which he was sitting, said Capt. Ken Koperski.
   The officers struggled briefly with McBeth and a woman also in
the car and said they noticed McBeth trying to swallow something,
Koperski said.
   ``He (McBeth) told the officers that he had swallowed cocaine so
they couldn't arrest him for possession,'' Koperski said.
   McBeth was taken to Mercy Hospital, where he told doctors he had
consumed about seven grams of the drug, some of it crack. Doctors
said he died in the emergency room of cardiac arrest caused by an
overdose, Koperski said.
   An autopsy was ordered.
