<HEAD>Four Sentenced For Attacking Theater Showing `Last Temptation'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANGERS, France (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four people were given short, suspended
sentences and fines Wednesday for attacking a theater last fall
showing the film ``The Last Temptation of Christ.''
   The four were convicted of throwing tear gas bombs and pouring
acid on seats in September and October at a movie theater in Angers,
about 180 miles southwest of Paris.
   Etienne Morcille, 25, was given a three-month suspended sentence
for tossing a tear gas bomb and for giving acid to another
unidentified man and two unidentified women, each of whom were given
two-month suspended sentences.
