<HEAD>Van Gogh Drawing Fetches $311,284</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS grafs 1-2 to CORRECT day of week to Thursday.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MECHLIN, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small colored drawing by Vincent van
Gogh of a woman with a folded umbrella fetched $311,284 at an
auction Thursday, more than three times the amount paid for it at an
auction in 1986.
   The sale at the Bernaerts auction house and art gallery ended
early Thursday after more than four hours of bidding.
   ``Sien With Umbrella,'' a crayon-and-pencil drawing van Gogh made
in 1883, went to an unidentified Belgian acting as an intermediary,
said Mon Bernaerts, the gallery's owner. It was bought for the art
trade, not for private ownership, he added.
   The drawing was sold for about $93,385 at an auction in 1986.
   In 1987, the van Gogh painting ``Irises,'' sold for $53.9 million
and ``Sunflowers'' went for $41.3 million.
   ``Sien With Umbrella'' measures only 18{-by-9.2 inches, and is a
drawing of a young woman, a folded umbrella under her right arm.
