<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A truck traveling north from Birmingham in central
England spilled thousands of hypodermic needles along a highway on
Thursday and about 75 drivers later reported flat tires, police said.
   ``The needles were scattered for one to two miles but it could
have been 10 or 15 miles before a motorist noticed his tires going
down,'' said a West Midlands police officer.
   ``We believe we have traced the lorry (truck) driver and he could
