<FIRST>r i AM-Spain-Chess     03-02 0138</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Spain-Chess,0143</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ivanchuk Keeps Lead In Tournament</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LINARES, Spain (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Vasili Ivanchuk of the Soviet Union held
the lead in the Seventh City of Linares chess tournament Thursday
after the 10th round of play.
   Ivanchuk drew with former world champion Anatoli Karpov, also of
the Soviet Union.
   Alexander Beliavsky of the Soviet Union defeated fellow Soviet
Artur Yusupov and Valeri Gulkov of the United States drew with
Soviet Andrei Sokolov.
   Two matches were adjourned: Jan Timman of Netherlands against
Johan Hjartarson of Iceland, and Nigel Short of Britain against
Yugoslavia's Ljbomir Ljubojevic.
   Lajos Portisch of Hungary did not play Thursday.
   Ivanchuk led the standings with 6 points, followed by Karpov with
5.5; Ljubojevic with 4.5; Yusupov with 4; Portisch, Short and Gulkov
with 3.5 each; Timman, Hjartarson and Beliavsky with 3 each; and
Sokolov with 2.5.
</TEXT>
