<FIRST>r i AM-Shipwreck     03-02 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Shipwreck,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Nigerian Ship Toll Now 11 Dead, 11 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LISBON, Portugal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Five more bodies from a wrecked Nigerian
cargo ship washed onto the coast Wednesday, bringing known deaths
from the wreck to 11 with 11 additional crewmembers still missing
and feared dead, rescue officials said.
   The 3,000-ton River Gurarra ran aground and broke up near Cape
Espichel, about 25 miles south of Lisbon, on Sunday after developing
engine trouble in gale-force winds and 16-foot waves.
   Air and sea rescue teams picked up 27 survivors in lifeboats
Sunday.
   ``We're working on the basis that there are no (further)
survivors,'' said Cmdr. Carlos Fidalgo of the navy's coastal command.
   The Nigerian news agency NAN reported Tuesday that 49 people had
been on board.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
