<FIRST>r f BC-Britain-Edelman     03-02 0210</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Britain-Edelman,0218</SECOND>
<HEAD>Edelman Lifts Storehouse Stake To 7 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Storehouse PLC said Thursday that American takeover
strategist Asher B. Edelman has raised his stake in the British
retailing group to 7 percent from 6.1 percent.
   Edelman notified Storehouse that he increased his holdings Friday
to 28.8 million shares, continuing the slow stakebuilding begun late
last year, the company said.
   Storehouse first discovered Edelman on its share register Dec. 6,
when it believed the holding amounted to 20 million shares, or 4.9
percent.
   Edelman later wrote the company saying he would like Storehouse
to undergo a restructuring or management buyout as a means of
improving shareholder value. His request to meet with the company to
discuss his plans was turned down.
   A Storehouse spokesman, who wasn't identified, in accordance with
British custom, said Thursday the company's contact with Edelman has
been limited to the formal notifications concerning his minority
stake.
   The company last month announced a string of measures to contain
costs, generate cash and improve operating efficiency to combat poor
trading prospects in the British retail sector.
   Storehouse, which is chaired by Sir Terence Conran, operates
about 980 stores in Britain, Europe and the United States under a
variety of names including Conran's, Habitat and Mothercare.
</TEXT>
