<HEAD>Copper Company Names New Chairman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Douglas C. Yearley, a Phelps Dodge Corp. vice
president, will replace G. Robert Durham as chairman and chief
executive of North America's largest copper producer, Durham said
Thursday.
   The change in leadership will take place after the company's May
3 annual meeting, Durham said in a prepared statement.
   Durham has announced his retirement June 30.
   Yearley, 53, is president of the Phelps Dodge Industries
division. His elevation will coincide with that of Leonard R. Judd,
49, another vice president, to president and chief operating officer
of Phelps Dodge.
   Both men are members of the board of directors, which elected
Yearley and Judd to their new positions during a meeting Wednesday.
   Yearley, educated at Cornell and Harvard universities, joined
Phelps Dodge in 1960. Judd, who attended the University of Arizona
to earn two degrees, joined the company in 1963.
   Phelps Dodge has operations throughout the United States and in
22 other countries.
