<HEAD>Judge Approves $4 Million Agreement Over Yugo</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEWARK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A $4 million management and finance agreement
was approved for Yugo America Inc., the importer of Yugoslavian-made
minicars that has filed for bankruptcy protection.
   The agreement, approved Wednesday by U.S. Bankruptcy Judge
Vincent J. Commisa, replaces an interim pact and is expected to keep
Yugo operating at least for another four months.
   Yugo and parent Global Motors Inc. filed for protection from
creditors under Chapter 11 of the federal bankruptcy law on Jan. 30.
   Commisa said he may rule next week on whether to allow a
Columbus, Ohio, liquidator, Norauto Ltd., to sell 4,700 Yugos, which
Norauto says it acquired in a purchase agreement.
   Yugo contends the agreement represented an extension of credit,
and says the cars' sale could lead to its collapse.
